title.narrative: ENABLING ENVIRONMENT - SECOND DECADE

description.narrative: By 2023, the government has increased capacity to legislate, plan and budget effectively on gender sensitive, multi-sector adolescent friendly services., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2023, adolescents are learning, healthy, developing and participating in an environment free from violence, exploitation and abuse.

description.narrative: Data Must Speak (DMS) remains at the forefront of planning and budgeting in education and is introduced to child welfare to encourage the publication and use of existing administratively collected data. The Violence Against Children and Youth Report launched in 2021 is used for prioritisation of interventions. Adolescent participation in various areas of programming will strengthen programme effectiveness and accountability to affected populations. Although Namibia boasts an overall solid normative framework, UNICEF has continued to support legal and policy reform to ensure its goals of quality inclusive education, child protection and adolescent health are being promoted.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/12/2021
